<body>
    <h1>Embeddable UI for KYC / KYB</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"95a801e4401f" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-Overview=
">Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2b0ac1925498">Interro will have a white-label, embeddable UI=
 component whose purpose is to collect identity and entity information from=
 end users and route it to the KYC and Risk Review Microservice for verific=
ation. It supports configurable branding and document collection flows to s=
erve multiple application clients.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"d13be068-3357-49d8-9c78-d7ad44357f89">
<h2 local-id=3D"dc8c16864fce" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-ClientContext=E2=
=80=94Verivend">Client Context =E2=80=94 Verivend</h2>
<p local-id=3D"6820e5a41fd6">The first client is <strong>Verivend</strong>,=
 a capital raising and investor portal platform serving General Partners (G=
Ps) and Limited Partners (LPs).</p>
<p local-id=3D"e360a39a320b">Verivend has historically allowed GPs to manag=
e KYC for their own investors, enabling rapid LP onboarding without a verif=
ication gate. Certain sensitive capabilities =E2=80=94 such as registering =
multiple bank accounts against an LP organization =E2=80=94 now require Ver=
ivend to perform direct LP KYC. A parallel need exists on the GP side: Veri=
vend has historically verified GPs manually through an admin-driven process=
, and automating that workflow is a strategic priority.</p>
<p local-id=3D"244b9baad3e1">Verivend will use Interro to collect informati=
on required for KYC across three verification paths: <strong>Individual (So=
lo)</strong>, <strong>Individual (Joint Account)</strong>, and <strong>Enti=
ty</strong>. The component owns the collection experience end-to-end. Veriv=
end owns the surrounding workflow, path selection, and verification lifecyc=
le. Verification outcomes surface in Verivend's native UI =E2=80=94 the com=
ponent collects and submits; it does not display results.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"a1389f49-554a-4eff-95aa-d3903c831431">
<h2 local-id=3D"a9a07988ddce" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-IntegrationModel=
">Integration Model</h2>
<p local-id=3D"7555c14e83e1">Verivend integrates with Interro through three=
 channels:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"6fc2683d-39a9-4cd2-b9ff-3fe805ddbcbe">
<li local-id=3D"48f206e7-6ac6-4ffb-9f08-d2d035534d49">
<p local-id=3D"bf8ccce788d1"><strong>Client-side events</strong> emitted by=
 the embedded component for real-time UX coordination (step progress, navig=
ation, errors)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ebda9bb8-a579-4e7d-a679-9992d4f6986e">
<p local-id=3D"bde870fff85c"><strong>Server-side webhooks</strong> delivere=
d by Interro for asynchronous lifecycle updates (submission, screening resu=
lts, abandonment detection), HMAC-signed with retry guarantees</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d90b0e19-2f75-410c-9c8a-63a5573adfb3">
<p local-id=3D"8f6b81d4014d"><strong>REST retrieval API</strong> for on-dem=
and access to applicant data, documents, and screening outcomes</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"ac5990990bcf" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-CoreArchitectura=
lConstraint">Core Architectural Constraint</h3>
<p local-id=3D"aac8068af8a5">Additional persons required for multi-person f=
lows (joint account co-holders, entity beneficial owners and directors) are=
 frequently not Verivend platform users and may never be. Their identity ve=
rification must occur outside the Verivend portal via token-authenticated s=
tandalone links served by Interro. This <strong>two-surface model</strong> =
=E2=80=94 embedded component for the primary user, standalone links for add=
itional persons =E2=80=94 is a core design constraint for the MVP.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"89bc932e-a5b6-4654-8ecb-de725845a8a1">
<h2 local-id=3D"3a8ddcc9c36f" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-MVPRequirements"=
>MVP Requirements</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"109feb6386e6" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-ConfigurableBran=
ding">Configurable Branding</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"7c724ea4-4f2e-4cab-ba2a-f20b2912cbbd">
<li local-id=3D"f6854b23-8ee5-40cd-a689-ddff67daf8a4">
<p local-id=3D"10d7f196aad3">Ability to configure primary, accent, heading,=
 and text colors per application client</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"00b72092-2f5e-422e-b349-dfa97f3f3ced">
<p local-id=3D"ee3624f177e3">Ability to configure the font per application =
client</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5bca435f-a8b8-4ba1-92c7-5176affbd2b1">
<p local-id=3D"c8efa2dfe551">Ability to configure a client logo or wordmark=
; "Powered by Interro" lockup is always present and must meet a defined min=
imum size and placement specification</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"40da56eb-5447-4a77-b54f-0f082476a5d8">
<p local-id=3D"677bae2352a9">Client-supplied color configurations must be v=
alidated against WCAG 2.1 AA minimum contrast ratios at configuration time;=
 a warning must be surfaced for non-compliant values</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d16cf7c8-c482-4f08-b02d-3f0e22b91af3">
<p local-id=3D"8f6b41fb34e1">Standalone verification links must be branded =
consistently with the host client's active theme configuration</p></li>
</ul>
<blockquote local-id=3D"8f641861-1bd1-4484-a05d-9afed7309ef3">
<p local-id=3D"9117a280f13f"><strong>Open Question =E2=80=94 Alloy Disclosu=
re:</strong> Is disclosure of Alloy's involvement required within the compo=
nent UI per the Alloy MSA?</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"3d18f59d-24c4-4047-b54e-ccf27496f776">
<h3 local-id=3D"01be639db691" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-VerificationPath=
s">Verification Paths</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"f0=
70dac1-d344-441f-8b77-db36dca2e192" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"05636f3e-5207-44fe-9b3a-617324aca759">
<th data-local-id=3D"299e9347-3dc0-4ed1-8f2e-f97b53160aa3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6359e386b5af">Path</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"6bb823a3-c472-41dd-be8f-2d7298a94f6c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"afea3b4291c7">Description</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"7850420c-b20b-44f0-99d9-52b6d5a70af5" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"0e81b82a4c8d">Steps</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"0915c2a5-200b-498b-baad-43f60a3bcbc4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e531d6248384">Persons KYC'd</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"46bce399-0b25-4a71-95cb-f2295de6d71a">
<td data-local-id=3D"1987b24c-e350-4669-bc18-bc5fabaec739" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"79de98bc10b2">Individual (Solo)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8a4c20d6-6c0f-472f-8b75-0a1e4c7f3029" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"647365b3e895">Single natural person</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b4db9cbb-3abc-4f73-97cd-04fa8d6acb6d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7de45c152b66">4</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0a7cf78a-64bb-43a6-91a0-e85b1ed774aa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6a6fe15f338e">1</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cbe26583-6273-4bd0-b466-670a2daea22d">
<td data-local-id=3D"b74312ad-8aa3-4e3a-995e-5181cfe97742" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3924da71e197">Individual (Joint Account)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7b678c1b-30cf-4640-bfa2-f74cdcdf57a9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a450b354c71a">2=E2=80=935 co-equal natural persons</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"127b4d2d-729e-4093-9475-c8e8a1265c6d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"774cbbafa7f5">5</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e84f039b-8972-417f-826a-5246f159aeee" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"881f4ce3de58">Each holder independently</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ee854517-2a39-4782-848a-961505b98b32">
<td data-local-id=3D"6d403906-0c8f-452f-aa7f-b1892b43baaf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1044f6899844">Entity</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"50f88b71-22ea-4bd2-b8ba-ec0603264c1a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"11d922de869a">LLC, Corporation, Trust, Partnership, etc.</p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8729e13c-870a-40d0-a13c-32d22b039aee" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4574919af738">5</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5dab1d1a-6fb2-48a6-a334-6cacef7e07d4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"49df9590ea08">1 authorized representative + N beneficial own=
ers (=E2=89=A525% ownership)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"9fb4d0a2-25e0-4a0c-a4a7-8d211ffa0e95">
<h3 local-id=3D"d6800f87c8cd" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-ContextIDsandIDV=
FlowOptions">Context IDs and IDV Flow Options</h3>
<p local-id=3D"da5fe343c942">Interro will offer multiple user flow options =
out of the box, selectable via Context ID:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f5eb674d-2422-400d-8bdd-784f0401ec04">
<li local-id=3D"b450b959-2286-4b2f-86a0-c7111ab6f497">
<p local-id=3D"6c2bab35b223"><strong>KYC Basic</strong> =E2=80=94 Does not =
instantiate the selfie step in the IDV workflow.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b60f23a7-f867-4eb2-94b5-5b5436dda7ce">
<p local-id=3D"11465f382b43"><strong>KYC Complete</strong> =E2=80=94 Includ=
es the selfie step in the IDV workflow.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c7a4f3e10d43">It is up to Product to work with Alloy to make=
 these Journeys available. For Verivend's Phase 1 integration =E2=80=94 whe=
re Interro will be used only for internal KYC of LPs =E2=80=94 only <strong=
>KYC Complete</strong> is required.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bb3cbaac7cb6">When a Context ID is not supplied during sessi=
on initialization, the default is <strong>KYC Complete</strong>.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c08d262a-6a17-42c6-85b0-686d48199d00">
<h3 local-id=3D"fc1e23dc801c" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-Multi-PersonOrch=
estration">Multi-Person Orchestration</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"4e84abe6169f" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-Two-PhaseModel">=
Two-Phase Model</h4>
<p local-id=3D"40d2ea0cc0ba"><strong>Phase 1 =E2=80=94 Primary User</strong=
></p>
<p local-id=3D"bc35d552f068">The Verivend account holder enters biographica=
l data for all additional persons (name, DOB, address). SSN and equivalent =
government ID numbers are <strong>not</strong> collected in this phase.</p>
<p local-id=3D"850f0a221258"><strong>Phase 2 =E2=80=94 Additional Persons</=
strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"9fd70edb1602">Each additional person receives a token-authen=
ticated verification link via email and SMS. IDV must be completed by the i=
ndividual.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6cbc29df-5214-4263-8585-25d182ba9a4f">
<li local-id=3D"e5e5ffcd-de63-4067-9b1d-dd6a3edc4f52">
<p local-id=3D"5d17e23d3b79"><strong>"Verify Now"</strong>, <strong>"Copy L=
ink"</strong>, and <strong>"Send to Email"</strong> must be available to de=
liver the IDV workflow per person</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c2542ad6-1684-434d-a3dc-d36cb4ed7ca4">
<p local-id=3D"a52315d25f1e">Real-time aggregate progress must be visible</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8605d457-549d-4624-9da8-2b17e729bf88">
<p local-id=3D"ac75076bdcfa">Reminder and resend must be supported</p></li>
</ul>
<blockquote local-id=3D"e593860b-48e2-4681-b72f-80c443f8ea13">
<p local-id=3D"268f4d8df10f"><strong>Open Question =E2=80=94 Reminder Sched=
ule:</strong> Should reminder timing be client-defined or system-defined? A=
dd initiation in status.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote local-id=3D"7c799ae8-98e3-48a5-a323-4a964e684b10">
<p local-id=3D"b3f2b049c38f"><strong>Action Item:</strong> Confirm with Ver=
ivend that additional party SSNs are not required for KYB or Joint Account =
Holder flows. This allows the primary user to enter name, address, and DOB =
for additional persons in the entity or joint account flow. With this confi=
rmation, a dedicated Interro-hosted data entry site for additional persons =
is not needed =E2=80=94 the IDV link can be sent directly to their email, t=
he primary user can open the IDV link if the additional person is nearby or=
 has a copy of their scanned ID, or the primary user can copy the IDV workf=
low link via the copy link button.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"2dcea096-def9-46f0-ae43-ff710697f524">
<h3 local-id=3D"6e733e493ea1" id=3D"EmbeddableUIforKYC/KYB-SessionInitializ=
ationContract">Session Initialization Contract</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"13=
6ae24b-0ad2-489d-b233-3aa7923676b6" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4bee4a7a-c586-4e06-9800-42dbf6d094bc">
<th data-local-id=3D"047d7eb2-8fe6-4e0a-b96e-abd0ed6db944" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"43697a0200b6">Parameter</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"7d6073c4-a68b-45bd-a1cc-5a4619bba670" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"068d8e97896c">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"cd1c9cae-71ad-4a60-aca1-4caef761430b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"53b8456b7562">When Passed</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"749841ac-3637-4b8c-a263-b731ac04f5f2">
<td data-local-id=3D"4c42a3d1-c34f-46f5-bb04-388d4ef8919a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"03bfa703a94d">Path type</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a3be342b-8643-49ba-a479-221d420c8d17" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5dba96dcd6b3"><code>individual</code> / <code>joint</code> /=
 <code>entity</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fd4ed9c3-6a2b-4d15-8d53-68e6797be1e0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dd6f5e5ec16d">Always</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c9d0889f-f401-45b2-afb0-4e0ae4866e44">
<td data-local-id=3D"d56eec7d-e447-4b05-a02f-6941f19c5e39" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a5787d26906b">Joint account type</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0f7591fd-82d9-46cb-b39b-6934f22fa019" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"da02053f0b4a"><code>JTWROS</code> / <code>TIC</code></p></td=
>
