<td data-local-id=3D"0f6b6d72-ee25-4050-9073-ed0e8c443906" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2bdfe85794ba">Supported</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e9ec96d2-ae0e-4b37-a60f-785284aa9b79">
<td data-local-id=3D"bd75ec66-6cac-41c8-a410-30a699523a5f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"929e5343937d"><strong>iframe vs JS SDK</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"678f6c08-a2b8-4624-8683-1cd0d3556947" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2aa16f51bf4c">iframe</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ba1e6ed0-cc46-4856-9544-e5f30154e769">
<td data-local-id=3D"abcdcede-86b7-42b8-932e-ad05c8e3c732" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bab911a85a0d"><strong>UI Resize</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"12563949-7c08-4f8d-a379-58872fa64388" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"49958426ea2e">Mobile-first. Component renders at a fixed mob=
ile-friendly width with internal scroll. Host application is responsible on=
ly for embedding the iframe and allocating space =E2=80=94 no resize coordi=
nation required.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e6fada2235b0">
<td data-local-id=3D"ffdd63c7-55f2-41ff-a685-8fba0b577c9e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"86e713ae42db">UBO Threshold</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"086eb8cb-84a3-4060-85a9-ae09da57f0d3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fbeb3aa13a82"><strong>For MTL Holders:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"324d0cc62be3"><strong>25% Baseline.</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"c1935c847898">A 10% threshold is required dynamically based =
on the MSB's internal risk assessment for high-risk transactional corridors=
, foreign nested services, or to satisfy specific state supervisory exams.<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"0f4b6d501362"><em>Law Cited: 31 CFR =C2=A7 1010.230; 31 CFR =
=C2=A7 1022.210.</em></p>
<p local-id=3D"02f38a170f9a"><strong>For GPs:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"f71e32cd9d00"><strong>25% Baseline.</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"7401e0c1f76a">A 10% threshold is frequently contractually ma=
ndated by upstream clearing banks, institutional LPs, or when funds possess=
 offshore capital from high-risk jurisdictions.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e7ead5fe1715"><em>Law Cited: 31 CFR =C2=A7 1010.230; 2024 Fi=
nal Rule (31 CFR =C2=A7 1010.100(t)).</em></p>
<p local-id=3D"59137f73d82b"><strong>For Broker Dealers: </strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"8f271c31cc24"><strong>25% Baseline.</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"cf14871a41ed">A 10% threshold is legally mandated for foreig=
n correspondent accounts and is routinely implemented for high-risk entitie=
s under FINRA rules.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f9bb3a955767"><em>Law Cited: 31 CFR =C2=A7 1010.230; 31 CFR =
=C2=A7 1010.610(b)(3)(ii)(A)</em></p>
<p local-id=3D"d22b20baf807"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bd8b4c2d1493">
<td data-local-id=3D"f11f734a-ae9e-4e8f-9609-e3c4e465f343" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4eba5d127634">When is proof of address required?</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"46854b78-fe38-4fb9-b4f3-bc88fd5c408f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9d57871c2d43"><strong>Summary: </strong>Might be required in=
 EDD workflows, not required for KYC.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b64ead44cc7d"><strong>For MTL Holders:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"d1f0f782eb90"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Documentary p=
roof of address (e.g., utility bill, lease agreement) is triggered when non=
-documentary verification fails, when an individual conducts a non-face-to-=
face transaction exceeding $3,000, or when issuing prepaid access over $10,=
000 and the provided address cannot be corroborated by independent data bur=
eaus.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b85f666245b0"></p>
<p local-id=3D"be2f64a5589b"></p>
<p local-id=3D"9442420a3568"><strong>Law Cited:</strong> 31 CFR =C2=A7 1022=
.210(d)(1)(i)(A) (MSB AML Program) [<a class=3D"external-link" data-card-ap=
pearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1022.21=
0" local-id=3D"7ab3f327-8a9b-4cc3-9a6b-c192f2b76560" rel=3D"nofollow">https=
://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1022.210</a> ]<sup>2</sup>; 31 CFR =C2=
=A7 1010.312 (Identification required) [<a class=3D"external-link" data-car=
d-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/101=
0.312" local-id=3D"41b21d8b-6f8c-446e-8452-b9d1530d2b3a" rel=3D"nofollow">h=
ttps://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1010.312</a> ].</p>
<p local-id=3D"cafa2bde189b"><strong>For GPs:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"e532d07d8f0c"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Documentary p=
roof is required when the individual lacks a standard residential street ad=
dress (necessitating verification of an APO/FPO or next-of-kin address), or=
 when the adviser utilizes non-documentary methods (e.g., credit bureau che=
cks) that return a substantive discrepancy regarding the individual's state=
d physical location.</p>
<p local-id=3D"40509dd21d54"></p>
<p local-id=3D"eacc14d05a99"></p>
<p local-id=3D"a41462c4c3b1"><strong>Law Cited:</strong> Proposed 31 CFR =
=C2=A7 1032.220(a)(2)(i)(A)(3) (Address Collection) [<a class=3D"external-l=
ink" href=3D"https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2024/05/21/2024-1073=
8/customer-identification-programs-for-registered-investment-advisers-and-e=
xempt-reporting-advisers" rel=3D"nofollow"><u>https://www.federalregister.g=
ov/documents/2024/05/21/2024-10738/customer-identification-programs-for-reg=
istered-investment-advis</u></a></p>
<p local-id=3D"8512c43c93f8"><strong>For Broker Dealers:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"f1d23b1acbe3"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Triggered spe=
cifically when the individual cannot present an unexpired government-issued=
 photo ID containing their current residential address, when the broker-dea=
ler is unfamiliar with the documents presented, or when the account is open=
ed entirely digitally (non-face-to-face) and automated identity cross-refer=
encing fails.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b6110d613382"></p>
<p local-id=3D"322b592ad139"></p>
<p local-id=3D"6016ef74f79a"><strong>Law Cited:</strong> 31 CFR =C2=A7 1023=
.220(a)(2)(ii)(B)(2) (Non-documentary verification triggers) [<a class=3D"e=
xternal-link" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.corne=
ll.edu/cfr/text/31/1023.220" local-id=3D"6b69ecbc-0c51-4159-b282-7d7db43569=
e6" rel=3D"nofollow">https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1023.220</a> ]=
.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"807b9d015450">
<td data-local-id=3D"29933e12-9a77-412a-9099-61354daadbb6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fb17a9263c99">What documents are required to be collected fr=
om an Entity to complete KYB?</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"387fa54c-34cc-418e-b37c-ac87fe0d2ffb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"48fb7bd9e159"><strong>For MTL Holders:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"bb58807d75d1"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Obtain docume=
nts establishing the entity's existence (e.g., articles of incorporation, b=
usiness licenses). This is strictly required when executing a transmittal o=
f funds of $3,000 or more, or when selling prepaid access exceeding $10,000=
 in a single day. The UI must capture the entity name, address, and Employe=
r Identification Number (EIN).</p>
<p local-id=3D"8d05fb499e23"></p>
<p local-id=3D"fd74cf5ca2b9"></p>
<p local-id=3D"ea55e6a63652"><strong>Law Cited:</strong> 31 CFR =C2=A7 1010=
.410(e) (Recordkeeping for transmittals) [<a class=3D"external-link" data-c=
ard-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1=
010.410" local-id=3D"e907790a-fae5-46b5-89ce-92dd10927004" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1010.410</a> ]<sup>1</sup>; 31 CFR=
 =C2=A7 1022.210(d)(1)(iv) (Prepaid access) [<a class=3D"external-link" dat=
a-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/3=
1/1022.210" local-id=3D"2a818ec8-77f3-495b-b8d5-0e5620e88a64" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1022.210</a> ].<sup>2</sup></p>
<p local-id=3D"5e28fda857fa"></p>
<p local-id=3D"167b6b486786"><strong>For GPs:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"6c2fd512a240"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Obtain certif=
ied formation documents (articles of incorporation, partnership agreements,=
 trust instruments). Additionally, under the CDD Rule, the UI must present =
the Appendix A Certification Form to collect Beneficial Ownership Informati=
on (BOI) identifying natural persons with 25% ownership or significant mana=
gerial control.</p>
<p local-id=3D"990d4511bfb1"></p>
<p local-id=3D"1881f4671943"></p>
<p local-id=3D"ad3aa4ff4e3b"><strong>Law Cited:</strong> Proposed 31 CFR =
=C2=A7 1032.220 (CIP for Investment Advisers) [<a class=3D"external-link" d=
ata-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.federalregister.gov/docu=
ments/2024/05/21/2024-10738/customer-identification-programs-for-registered=
-investment-advisers-and-exempt-reporting-advisers" local-id=3D"27175e16-24=
a1-4798-a441-94e7f73fb0b2" rel=3D"nofollow">https://www.federalregister.gov=
/documents/2024/05/21/2024-10738/customer-identification-programs-for-regis=
tered-investment-advisers-and-exempt-reporting-advisers</a> ]<sup>4</sup></=
p>
<p local-id=3D"e3b7d8ddf415"></p>
<p local-id=3D"a743f5c7d1dc"><strong>For Broker Dealers: </strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"51053c18c9a1"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Obtain docume=
nts showing the legal existence of the entity, explicitly including certifi=
ed articles of incorporation, a government-issued business license, a partn=
ership agreement, or a trust instrument. The UI must also mandate the colle=
ction of the FinCEN BOI certification to fulfill CDD obligations.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f34c4b0e8050"></p>
<p local-id=3D"ddb58392c626"></p>
<p local-id=3D"6ad831df3080"><strong>Law Cited:</strong> 31 CFR =C2=A7 1023=
.220(a)(2)(ii)(A)(2) (Broker-Dealer CIP) [<a class=3D"external-link" data-c=
ard-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1=
023.220" local-id=3D"54a7eeed-d20f-4185-8ca9-d3a30cdfdc22" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1023.220</a> ]<sup>6</sup>; 31 CFR=
 =C2=A7 1010.230 (CDD Rule) [<a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearanc=
e=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1010.230" loca=
l-id=3D"3201fac4-6137-4cb6-8b9b-ce40d8e3011e" rel=3D"nofollow">https://www.=
law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1010.230</a> ].</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ea557f0a5042">
<td data-local-id=3D"5f25879e-5564-4c35-b649-02c7f80b47bc" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e21c693d0993">How many UBOs and Control Persons must KYC be =
run on to satisfy KYB as part of an AML Program?</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f56af9ac-f636-4fcc-89cf-3bf08d27f3bd" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bd5138957396"><strong>Targets:</strong> UBOs (=E2=89=A525% e=
quity) and exactly 1 Control Person.</p>
<p local-id=3D"79b4c7c2811d"></p>
<p local-id=3D"5dfcff655e12"></p>
<p local-id=3D"34ff8fa2c109"><strong>0 UBOs Acceptable?</strong> Yes. If no=
 individual holds =E2=89=A525% equity directly or indirectly, 0 UBOs are re=
ported.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3e4c868062b1"></p>
<p local-id=3D"b6cea49f69f0"></p>
<p local-id=3D"74f0262c487a"><strong>0 Control Persons Acceptable?</strong>=
 No. A legal entity must <em>always</em> identify exactly one Control Perso=
n.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a514c6fbfd26"></p>
<p local-id=3D"0836fa6c559e"></p>
<p local-id=3D"01133b449b99"><strong>Citation:</strong> 31 CFR =C2=A7 1022.=
210 (Risk-based AML program) utilizing the definitive standard of 31 CFR =
=C2=A7 1010.230(d).</p>
<p local-id=3D"0c6eefb20235"></p>
<p local-id=3D"6de2b4820a87"></p>
<p local-id=3D"67c1da369f39"><strong>URL:</strong>(<a class=3D"external-lin=
k" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/=
text/31/1022.210" local-id=3D"efdfd425-60a2-4a9b-8d96-492d604cc0da" rel=3D"=
nofollow">https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1022.210</a> ) &amp;(<a c=
lass=3D"external-link" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://www.=
law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1010.230" local-id=3D"d9459d79-a55a-478a-a3dc-f=
cbb3ae04f38" rel=3D"nofollow">https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/31/1010.=
230</a> )</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"625693f264d7">
<td data-local-id=3D"b77b20fbf708" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa31d9bdb638"></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fed4fc1057cf" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fb81eebd6898"></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
